==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lumbosacral
<hw>Lum`bo*sa"cral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lumbus</ets> loin + E. <ets>sacral</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the loins and sacrum; <as>as, the
<ex>lumbosacral</ex> nerve, a branch of one of the lumber nerves which
passes over the sacrum</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lumbric</ent>⟦br⟧
